clue: This largest Belgian city is the seat of the European Union & known as the "Capital of Europe"

response: Brussels

clue: Long ruled by others, in 1815 Belgium was merged with this northern neighbor but became its own kingdom at last in 1830

response: the Netherlands

clue: 2 wins in the Tour of Flanders are among the record 525 in this sport by national hero Eddy "the Cannibal" Merckx

response: bicycle racing

clue: This large cultural & linguistic group lives in southern Belgium & speaks predominantly French

response: the Walloons

clue: In WWI the second battle of this western Belgian cit"Y" saw some of the earliest use of deadly poison gas

response: Ypres

